annotation.TEXT: Whoa, geez!
Ooh, there's some sort of gate up there. I'm guessing that's going to eventually be my final destination.
Alright, so let's take a look at those paths' progress here...
Level 33...
BGM: Super Mario Bros. - Metal Version
Oh, man. This one's tricky. You've gotta spin jump off of the Yukkuri Thwomps to reach the silver P-switch.

Actually, Patchy shouldn't be a huge threat, as she's only got a limited number of places she can appear, though I guess there's a slight chance of her appearing on the far right and transforming one of the turn blocks just as you get over there, which could be problematic if that happens.

Ooh, this one's also tricky, though I think it's a lot less luck-based than that pumpkin head one. Also, it's not quite as tricky as it first looks, as the sprite limit will reduce the Lava Lotuses' firing ability.
And, this one looks like another no-enemy platforming challenge. It's once again slippery, and be careful of the arrow blocks. I should be able to handle this without messing up horribly, right?
Level 31...
It's obvious that I've gotta use that Pitching Nitori to reach the upper enemies here. Aim carefully...
Sweet! That went perfectly! (Although, why did I only get 200 points when I landed on the shell at the end of that air combo? Shouldn't I have gotten 1000? Well, whatever. That's not important.)
Okay, watch out for the bullets, the Hina moles, and the caped Remilias here.
Due to their movement pattern, it tends to be easier to dodge below them than above them. Also, the ON/OFF block can be used as a powerful weapon to make this level much easier!

Oh, cool. Looks like the arrows don't affect me at all while I'm in the cloud. Also, don't waste too much time reaching the moon with the cloud. You wouldn't want it to vanish at the wrong time and Kaizo trap you!
BGM: Kid Icarus NES - Sky Palace (reused)
BGM: Bishoujo Senshi Sailor Moon: Another Story - Legendary Battle
The bouncy blocks near the goal shouldn't really affect you too much. Just be aware of them as you jump over the bullet cannons and you should be fine.
Level 32...
Okay, now to wait for LakiTewi to reappear, then smack her with Kisume and steal her cloud so I can reach the goal moon in the upper-left.
Level 37...

Hello, and welcome back to more Hakurei Adventure Mission! Since last time, I did a little bit of off screen Start+Selecting to position Reimu over here near Sanae and get the overworld music to come back. Now for level 30...
The cloud didn't vanish at all on me there, so I guess I had some leeway, time-wise.
Gee, who hasn't heard this song like a wixillion times already? (Though it still is a nice song.) Anyway, spin jump off the magic and watch out for Patchouli.
Haven't quite reached the upper-right palm tree yet...
BGM: Final Fantasy 4 - Boss Battle (reused)
To be continued...
Okay, we're halfway through this row. Next is level 35...
Get ready...
BGM: Mega Man 3 (Game Boy) - Wily's Marine Fortress

Ooh, boy. It's Rip Van Kitty! (Orin, perhaps?) Careful not to wake them up-- Oh, wait. It's kind of impossible to avoid waking them up. Well, just dodge them as you make your way to the ON/OFF block in the upper-right corner.
Okay, I remember seeing this one in Goron50's videos. First, let's make our way to the right, watching out for LakiTewi's attacks.
Once you make it back with the P-switch, hit it and wait for the silver coins to come to you.

Alright, so up next will be the 40s, and I'll be starting where it would've made more sense for level 39 to have been positioned. Why did they put level 39 in the upper-left like that anyway? Tune in next time, when we won't find out!
BGM: Kirby's Adventure - Nightmare (Final Form)
No way. Did I seriously pull that off on my first try?! I really expected this to be yet another Sanae death(s), and perhaps Reimu's first death(s). Holy cow, I must've gotten really lucky there!
Okay, what do we have here? It looks like it's just a platforming challenge with no spawning enemies appearing... Oh, and the floor is slippery. Okay, I can do this...

As a result, the right two plants will fail to fire the second time, so you can focus more on dodging Nitori's attacks. Oh, and in case you can't see it, there's an ON/OFF block above Nitori, which will dump the plants into the abyss when hit.
BGM: DKC2 - Stickerbrush Symphony

I'll just stomp LakiTewi to take her out of the picture for a moment here. Oh, I got lucky that her spiny didn't fall where the ON/OFF switch was. Speaking of which, make sure that the Kisume above won't fall into the central pit when you hit the switch. You'll need her.
I'm nearing the end of the row. Level 38...
Alright, so this means I successfully got through this episode without a single death! Huzzah!
No, that actually went exactly as planned. Cool.
But, that's only half of the mission. Now, you've gotta get back to bring the silver P-switch back to the starting point! Watch out for that death ceiling above!
Now watch as I somehow screw this up in some stupid way...
Okay, I got through the anticipated quick-time event in one piece! Maybe I can complete this oddly-paletted room without dying after all (despite all the skulls and death symbols in the background)!
Done, finally. That waiting almost felt like the hardest part to me, but actually the hardest part is getting back to start with the silver P-switch.
Ohh... Why does waiting have to be so boring?
Sweet! Things are going well for me so far today! Maybe this will be an actual death-less episode? (Oh, crap. I didn't just jinx myself again, did I?)
I think I'll take out this last one the intended way, rather than grilled cheese it with the ON/OFF block.

Okay, now for level 39, which, oddly enough, isn't on the same horizontal line as the rest of the 30s, but is instead in the upper-left corner for some reason. Now I just know the game's gonna try to jinx me with some quick-reaction thing...

There's also the distinct possibility of her telefragging you just as you're about to hit the goal as well, so watch out for that I guess. Fortunately for me, I had good luck with her leaving me alone.
BGM: Ievan Polkka (the leekspin song)
BGM: RoboWarrior - Main Theme (reused)
Obviously, the intended solution is to use the ON/OFF blocks to open up a path to the green star so you can fry these kitties, but the ON/OFF block itself is capable of KO-ing them!
Now that's more of a skill-based win, unlike with those pumpkin heads Sanae got lucky with in the last level!
It might be a little tricky (and I nearly got bulleted back there), but it shouldn't be unreasonable unless you get unlucky and a Super Remilia ambushes you while you're near the edges of the level.
BGM: SMB3 - World 8 Map
Oh, god. It's one of Goron50's favorite levels. The goal is to stomp all of the pumpkin heads and land back at the start. Oh, and be aware that there's a ceiling off screen. Um... Good luck!
Level 34...
P-switch BGM: SMB3 - P-switch
Level 36...
Also, it's interesting how Reimu appears to get her PC-98 colors when she becomes fiery. Does this mean these would've been Sanae's colors if she existed in the PC-98 era?
